# Transcript Provider Pattern

## Architecture

All transcript sources implement `TranscriptProviderAdapter` from `lib/providers/base.ts` and register via `registerProvider()`. The pipeline never touches provider-specific logic — only the normalized `NormalizedTranscript` format.

## Adding a New Provider

1. Create `src/lib/providers/my-source.ts`
2. Implement the `TranscriptProviderAdapter` interface
3. Call `registerProvider(myProvider)` at module level
4. Add a webhook route at `src/app/api/webhooks/my-source/route.ts`

```typescript
import { registerProvider, type TranscriptProviderAdapter } from "./base";
import type { NormalizedTranscript } from "@/lib/types";

const myProvider: TranscriptProviderAdapter = {
  name: "my-source",

  async initialize(config) { /* one-time setup */ },
  async startListening() { /* begin watching */ },
  async stopListening() { /* cleanup */ },

  validateWebhook(headers, body) {
    return headers["x-webhook-secret"] === process.env.WEBHOOK_SECRET;
  },

  parseWebhook(body) {
    // Extract external ID from webhook payload
    return { externalId: (body as { id: string }).id };
  },

  async fetchTranscript(externalId): Promise<NormalizedTranscript> {
    // Fetch and normalize into common format
    return { provider: "my-source", externalId, /* ... */ };
  },
};

registerProvider(myProvider);
```

## Key Rules

- All provider-specific parsing stays inside the adapter — never leak raw formats downstream
- Deduplication is handled by the ingestion service via `(provider, external_id)` unique constraint
- Add the provider name to the `TranscriptProvider` union type in `lib/types/index.ts`
- Add it to `active_providers` config for the setup page to recognize it
